The cutter will be checked instead by the driver from the ATM.
The ATM service that will work from tomorrow is very simple.
Simply insert the Opencard card and after payment of the cutting, it will load on it.
The electronic cards are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is in the urban lines of trains and buses from 300 to 499, which the inhabitants of the municipalities of Central Bohemia take to reach the capital.
"In the added trains in the integrated transports of Prague there are the controllers with the readers of the cards with which they verify the temporal and zonal validity," explained the mode of control of the Filip tickets by the organization Ropid, which develops the schedules of the collective transports of Prague.
Urban buses have card readers integrated into the driver's box.
During the climb it is therefore necessary not only to show the magnetic card to the driver, but also to support the Opencard at the point determined next to the case.
So the driver checks the validity of the loaded coupons.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the loaded coupons, there is nothing easier than asking the driver for this type of information," added Drápal.
Passengers who take urban buses and will not remember, when the validity of the cutting, can again go to the self-service ATMs, where they load the cutters on the paper.
