The Ministry of Internal Affairs requires drivers with three administrative penalties for excessive alcohol in their blood, to install in their car the system that prevents the vehicle from driving in a state of drunkenness or if it does not blow in the appropriate device.
The measure was announced last June and is already included in the annual report of the Attorney General's Office, according to which it will be a one-year pilot project.
The purpose of this project is to reintegrate the driver, since he will have to attend a rehabilitation course on the road.
In addition to the General Prosecutor's Office for Road Safety, the General Directorate of Traffic (DGT) and the Technological Institute for Automobile Safety (FITSA) will participate in this initiative.
According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of drivers reported more than once for drunk driving then return to drive the car.
The alcoholic would avoid this, because it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the alcohol rate in the breathed air and prevents the car from being started if the driver does not blow, or when a higher alcohol concentration is detected than the permitted one.
The cost is more than EUR 1000 and would be borne by the sanctioned person.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with such devices can reduce up to 65% of infringements committed during the first year of introduction.
And in Spain it is estimated that it could save the lives of 115 people a year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to stop these behaviours before they become criminal offences.
And in order to facilitate its development, since the legal reform can be carried out on an ordinary basis, and without a doubt the necessary reform for the criminal procedure would require an organic law.
However, the device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial solution, although it has already been introduced experimentally in some industrial and public vehicles.
