What was produced in the invoice factory of Zuschlag & partners?
The trial against János Zuschlag and his partners will be discussed shortly on 8 October.
Politicians and their associates are accused of repeated commercial fraud committed in the framework of a criminal association that has caused considerable damage, and of other crimes, including forgery of documents.
According to the Prosecutor's Office, the money obtained from tenders was used by them for private purposes, and they have often certified the carrying out of the activities through false invoices.
The state and municipal money, in total 65 million guilders, ended up in part in the caskets of the organization Fiatal Baloldal, in part in the pockets of some people.
According to the method, made known by the investigating authorities, they took the money obtained from tenders on the basis of invoices for non-existent transactions and the associations never fulfilled their obligations.
According to the indictment, most of the invoices were false.
To make them, the invoice blocks were purchased at the market of Józsefváros, the circular stamps instead were manufactured in Kiskunhalas.
And in order to decide on behalf of which companies to issue invoices, it was established, among other things, during the trip between the hills above Balaton where János Zuschlag had sent István Lados.
According to the confession of the latter he had to choose pensions and restaurants.
He asked for an invoice for the consumptions, on the model of these then were prepared the invoices to forward to the invitations of competition, among others, those of the Ministry for Youth and Sport, the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs and the Municipality of Budapest.
Most of these are the work of István Lados and András, who, according to our information, drew up the reports necessary to obtain the funding.
One of the choices of Lados' "study trip" was a brewery.
According to two invoices issued by Zuschlag and partners in 2003, the place of catering provided meals for a group of 90 people from the Biztos Pont Egyesület Association.
So many people, however, according to the restaurant owner, would not all enter the room together.
