The psychology of overbidding: why spend more money?
At auctions buyers are likely to spend more, overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and economists researchers at the University of New York have been able to discover the neuro-economic bases of this well-known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to their study published in Science magazine, men do not want to stay back in a race like eBay's auction, so they are willing to pay even a higher price.
The research tried to trace the nervous pattern of this "game" at the nervous system level through experimental auctions.
One group of volunteers played the lot, the other group of players participated in an auction while using the functional magnetic resonance method (fMRI) examined the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win money, but in the game of the auction, in which the substantial element is that of bidding more than the other, the body striated under the cerebral cortex comes into operation intensively when you lose in the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the "self-gratification" mechanism of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to the researchers, the price rise is explained by scanning the vehement reaction of the striated body.
To support their theory, the research group economists conducted a financial tracking survey.
In this investigation, three groups tendered against a partner under different conditions.
They reported to the control group how much the actual value of the product in question was and they made their bet.
To another group besides this they have promised that in the case of winning they will receive another prize of 15 dollars.
The third group, on the other hand, would have received $15 before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost the money in the event of the auction loss.
The difference between the two groups consisted in the fact that for one of them the winning was emphasized, while for the other the loss.
By testing the hypothesis of neurologists the members of the group playing "against loss" were willing to make higher bets of the control group or "winner".
"These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
These so far explained the phenomena found at auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurological image have helped to resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we have come to a third explanation" - said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when should you contact your doctor?
Nearly half a billion people in the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, while chronic liver disease is mentioned in Hungary as one of the leading causes of death.
In Hungary the number of hepatitis patients amounts to one hundred thousand, of which only 7,000 are treated: the reason is that many patients do not know they are infected.
The definition of hepatitis is the collective name of contagious liver diseases caused by different viruses.
There are many similarities between the symptoms, typical are hepatitis and jaundice, but their pathogens and the diseases caused differ from each other.
Hepatitis viruses spread in two main forms depending on the pathogen: hepatitis A and E via the food channel (e.g. water and infected foods), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and organic fluids (sperm, vaginal loss, saliva).
For travellers, it is useful to get vaccination against A and B, and there is no vaccine for C.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after eating infected foods, accompanied by general malaise, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After they form yellow spots on the skin and white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the urine dark, the healing takes place within two to three weeks.
One million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, which causes liver cancer and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason is, according to estimates, that only one in ten people receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if not treated it can cause liver cirrhosis and liver tumors.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because the pathogens subtly destroy the liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore it is very important to prevent and carry out regular medical analyses.
This disease is much more common than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In the world today, the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
Since a routine laboratory examination also reveals the disease, it is worth contacting your family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated by the body, thus ceasing the infectious power and preventing the formation of tumors.
September 30th is the World Day of Hepatitis, organized for the first time in 2004 worldwide by associations of patients.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and the early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the result of a recent investigation, religious faith functions as a kind of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
Scientists at Oxford University conducted an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God influences the feeling of pain, reported the British Telegraph.
As part of the bizarre investigation, an electroshock was carried out on 12 Catholic believers and as many atheists, while everyone observed a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for pain control.
The test is the first in a series of research in which scientists, philosophers and theologians of the University also take part, in addition to academics.
The test was carried out exactly like this: an instrument that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the experiment subject.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the Virgin Mary painted in the 17th century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the hermitage of Leonardo da Vinci painted in the 15th century.
The authors of the examination hoped that the image of the Virgin Mary would give rise to a sort of religious state among believers, while Leonardo's painting was chosen because it did not differ too much from the other and considered it to be of reassuring effect.
The subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this age range received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while observing either the religious-themed painting or the other.
The Catholics reported that the vision of the Virgin Mary made them feel "safe", as if "someone took care of" them and "they calmed down and were pervaded by peace".
Looking at the religious-themed image, they accounted for 12% less pain than when Leonardo's work was before them.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image with strong effect even for the atheists, but we must find the appropriate image.
"We must look for an image to which they have very positive feelings, such as a mother or a father" - said the psychologist.
Anglican Bishop Tom Wright welcomed the result of the research.
"The practice of faith should change, and in many cases it can change our personality." - added Wright.
After the excellent results only the question remains if the painting of a Madonna of Leonardo or another painter of such a calibre is presented to believers, what effect could it have on the control of pain?
Would the vision of a quality virgin Mary bring better results?
