Industry prices continue to rise
The prices of domestic industrial sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - informs the Central Institute of Hungarian Statistics.
Industry's export sales prices in July 2008 were 1.1% higher than in the previous year, but fell by 3.9%.
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than in the previous month and 3.2 % higher than in a year ago.
Domestic industrial sales prices compared to the previous month rose by only 0.1%.
Domestic sales prices in the processing sector also rose to a minimum by 0.1% compared to July.
The biggest increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially the bags and belts with 4.6% and the production of shoes with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price of plastic and chemical raw materials has led to a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum in the processing of wood (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector, prices increased in August by 0.3% in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in the gas price by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the manufacturing industries, the biggest increases were in the oil processing sector (32.4%).
In the manufacture of metal products, the price increase was 13.2%, 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco, which is a determining factor.
A fall in prices was observed in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry, the pace of price increases ranged from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the processing industry in the past year prices have risen by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded last year by 18.7%.
In domestic sales among the target groups of the sectors, the highest monthly price increase occurred in August in sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods prices rose by 0.3%, in the energy sector and in subsequent use prices did not change compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the increase in the largest prices was observed in the energy sector and subsequent use (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
Industrial export sales prices calculated in guilders rose in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared to 12 months, fell by 3.9%.
